London, as its new music director. The appointment of Quinn, 35, a
conductor whose experience has included work with major opera and
symphony orchestras as well as the recording of Paul McCartney's
recent composition, ``Tuesday,'' ends an unabashedly public search
by the company. In the last two years 12 guest conductors,
