   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   AMA-CUBANS _ As the American Medical Association board convenes
this week, its members could decide to step into a Florida dispute
over the licensing of foreign-trained physicians. Last year,
Florida became the only state in the nation to offer its own
medical licensing exam, an alternative to the United States Medical
Licensing Examination. Only about 450 people, mostly Cubans who
