</P>
<P>
   GLF-PEBBLE-NO7 _ The seventh hole at Pebble Beach. Site of this
week's U.S. Open, is one of the scariest shots in golf. Depending
upon the wind off the ocean, the 100-yard hold, a par 3, can be
anywhere from a sand wedge to a 3-iron. The hole is a perfect
combination of beauty and treachery, and it's where the Open can be
lost in a hurry. (Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
