<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBC-USC-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USC'S PERSELL COMES OUT OF NOWHERE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   OMAHA, Neb. - Considering no colleges recruited Josh Persell
when he graduated from Montclair Prep of Van Nuys four years ago,
there was little to suggest he would be USC's starting designated
hitter at the College World Series.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think a lot of people would be incredibly shocked about
me,'' Persell said. ``The experience is kind of surreal. But it's
the greatest baseball experience I've ever had. Perseverance is
what it takes.''
</P>
<P>
   Persell originally earned a spot on the Trojans roster after his
hitting instructor, Mike Cicione of Tarzana, asked USC coach Mike
Gillespie to give him a chance to make the team.
</P>
<P>
   Persell was a reserve walk-on for the Trojans his first two
years but didn't make the travel squad to Omaha when USC won the
College World Series in 1998. Last year, he appeared in 28 games
and hit .309 as a utility player.
</P>
<P>
   But it wasn't until this season that he found a regular spot at
designated hitter and been one of the team's biggest surprises.
</P>
<P>
   Persell went 2 for 3 and scored a run in USC's 6-4 victory over
Florida State on Saturday, and is hitting .346 with nine home runs
and 40 RBI.
</P>
<P>
   ``I kind of fell into a role,'' Persell said. ``It's kind of
overwhelming right now and a dream come true. When we drove into
the stadium here,it was like, `You finally made it.' ''
</P>
<P>
   Little ball: USC may be ranked fourth in the nation, but there
probably isn't a less physically imposing team at the College World
Series. No.1 pitcher Rik Currier is 5-foot-9. Catcher Beau Craig is
listed at 5-11, but about the same size as Currier. Second baseman
Anthony Lunetta is also listed at 5-9.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think we'll win the fight after a game,'' Gillespie
said. ``But baseball is still a game where normal-size people can
still play. Because I'm with them every day, I don't really think
about it. Until you play a team that is physical like Georgia Tech,
then you say `Wow.'''
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans' size hasn't made much difference, however, because
Craig has 17 home runs and Lunetta 12. As for Currier, he has a
15-3 record.
</P>
<P>
   Star power: As USC ended practice at Creighton University on
Sunday, Texas arrived for its scheduled workout. Among those
dressed in uniform and participating in the practice was actor
Kevin Costner.
</P>
<P>
   He is friends with Texas coach Augie Garrido, the longtime coach
at Costner's alma mater, Cal State Fullerton.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-11-00 2253EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
